<h2 id="quick-start">Quick Start</h2>

<p>Add this line to your application&#39;s Gemfile:</p>

<pre><code class="ruby">gem &quot;chartkick&quot;
</code></pre>

<p>For Rails 6 / Webpacker, run:</p>

<pre><code class="sh">yarn add chartkick chart.js
</code></pre>

<p>And in <code>app/javascript/packs/application.js</code>, add:</p>

<pre><code class="js">import &quot;chartkick/chart.js&quot;
</code></pre>

<p>For Rails 5 / Sprockets, in <code>app/assets/javascripts/application.js</code>, add:</p>

<pre><code class="js">//= require chartkick
//= require Chart.bundle
</code></pre>

<p>This sets up Chartkick with <a href="https://www.chartjs.org/">Chart.js</a>. For other charting libraries, see <a href="#installation">detailed instructions</a>.</p>

